1
00:00:06,601 --> 00:00:11,038
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,105 --> 00:00:14,632
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:14,709 --> 00:00:18,145
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,212 --> 00:00:21,807
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:21,883 --> 00:00:25,148
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,219 --> 00:00:27,153
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:28,957 --> 00:00:31,892
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:35,760
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,164 --> 00:00:43,002
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,237 --> 00:00:50,302
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:50,612 --> 00:00:56,744
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:56,884 --> 00:01:01,150
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,222 --> 00:01:04,817
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:04,892 --> 00:01:08,225
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,296 --> 00:01:11,925
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,595
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:15,670 --> 00:01:19,162
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:22,835
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:22,910 --> 00:01:27,006
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:45,377 --> 00:01:49,108
<i>I never thought he'd attempt to use</i>
<i>the Fourth Hokage's Jutsu.</i>

21
00:01:50,015 --> 00:01:51,880
<i>But it's still just this level...</i>

22
00:01:52,217 --> 00:01:54,777
<i>It's completely different</i>
<i>from the original one.</i>

23
00:01:55,887 --> 00:01:59,721
<i>That Tsunade...</i>
<i>Incredibly strong as always.</i>

24
00:02:01,126 --> 00:02:03,151
<i>I remember a long time ago,</i>

25
00:02:03,228 --> 00:02:06,527
<i>getting punched by her and</i>
<i>knocked back nearly 100 meters...</i>

26
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:11,660
<i>At any rate, Naruto's hopeless.</i>

27
00:02:12,304 --> 00:02:13,703
Are you okay?

28
00:02:15,073 --> 00:02:16,938
Jiraiya, was it you...

29
00:02:17,008 --> 00:02:18,942
who taught him that Rasengan,
the Spiral Chakura Sphere?

30
00:02:19,844 --> 00:02:20,970
<i>Rasengan...?!</i>

31
00:02:21,613 --> 00:02:25,640
I'm his teacher, after all.

32
00:02:26,218 --> 00:02:30,587
Humph... You and the Fourth Hokage are
the only ones who can use that Jutsu.

33
00:02:31,356 --> 00:02:33,916
Are you in your right mind...

34
00:02:33,992 --> 00:02:35,550
showing someone Jutsu
that he can't master?

35
00:02:36,661 --> 00:02:38,595
Don't give him false hope.

36
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:44,127
That's why the moony kid starts joking
about becoming a Hokage!

37
00:02:45,003 --> 00:02:48,439
It's no joke! Stupid! Stupid!

38
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,666
If I have three days,
I'll master this Jutsu!

39
00:02:52,978 --> 00:02:55,037
You said it, kid.

40
00:02:55,714 --> 00:02:57,443
Men don't go back on their word!

41
00:02:57,849 --> 00:03:01,216
Hah! I stand by my words.

42
00:03:02,454 --> 00:03:04,615
That's my Ninja Way.

43
00:03:10,128 --> 00:03:12,790
Then... how about a wager?

44
00:03:13,798 --> 00:03:14,730
A wager...?

45
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,765
I'll give you one week.

46
00:03:17,369 --> 00:03:19,769
If you can master that Jutsu,

47
00:03:20,171 --> 00:03:22,435
I'll acknowledge that you have
what it takes to become the Hokage

48
00:03:22,507 --> 00:03:24,475
and give you this necklace.

49
00:03:24,709 --> 00:03:27,735
Lady Tsunade! That's the precious...!

50
00:03:28,179 --> 00:03:30,909
I don't need such a sorry necklace!

51
00:03:31,249 --> 00:03:32,716
Don't say such things, Naruto...

52
00:03:33,084 --> 00:03:35,484
That's the only one of its kind in this world.

53
00:03:35,553 --> 00:03:37,453
And you could buy three mountains
if you were to sell it.

54
00:03:38,690 --> 00:03:41,181
It belonged to the First Hokage.

55
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,952
<i>A-Awesome...</i>

56
00:03:44,929 --> 00:03:47,124
Well, that'll be fine!

57
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,429
<i>He'll do anything for money...?</i>

58
00:03:50,802 --> 00:03:51,496
Good...

59
00:03:51,936 --> 00:03:56,396
However, you lose if you can't master
the Jutsu in one week!

60
00:03:56,975 --> 00:03:58,909
And you'll give me all the money
you have on you.

61
00:03:58,977 --> 00:04:00,376
Oh! Gama chan!

62
00:04:00,845 --> 00:04:01,573
When did she...?!

63
00:04:02,514 --> 00:04:04,175
Lady Tsunade! Why?

64
00:04:04,249 --> 00:04:05,375
That necklace is...

65
00:04:06,751 --> 00:04:08,184
He won't be able to do it, anyway...

66
00:04:08,586 --> 00:04:09,518
Let's go, Shizune.

67
00:04:10,622 --> 00:04:14,558
<i>She never once used</i>
<i>that necklace for a bet...</i>

68
00:04:17,062 --> 00:04:19,553
<i>You don't have to answer right now.</i>

69
00:04:20,231 --> 00:04:22,961
<i>However, I want it in a week.</i>

70
00:04:28,073 --> 00:04:33,978
<i>Inheritance!</i>
<i>The Necklace of Death!</i>

71
00:04:36,848 --> 00:04:40,545
Huh? Who is it this late at night?

72
00:04:41,353 --> 00:04:44,083
Okay, okay. I'm coming.

73
00:04:46,224 --> 00:04:50,183
I'm sorry to bother you so late, Naruto.
I need to talk to you...

74
00:04:51,196 --> 00:04:55,098
As for me, I'm going to get
a good night's rest and train tomorrow!

75
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:59,796
I'm sorry. But I didn't want you
to misunderstand Lady Tsunade...

76
00:05:01,172 --> 00:05:03,231
As well as the necklace...

77
00:05:04,209 --> 00:05:07,110
Humph! I could care less
about an old lady like that!

78
00:05:07,178 --> 00:05:09,544
Lady Tsunade is not the type
of person you think she is!

79
00:05:09,714 --> 00:05:12,649
Don't speak of her like that
when you don't even know her!

80
00:05:16,688 --> 00:05:18,781
I-I'm sorry... for raising my voice.

81
00:05:20,558 --> 00:05:23,322
She didn't used to be like that.

82
00:05:23,962 --> 00:05:27,420
She was a kind person
who loved the village.

83
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:31,268
But, she changed...

84
00:05:36,141 --> 00:05:37,540
After that day...

85
00:05:39,310 --> 00:05:40,242
That day?

86
00:05:43,281 --> 00:05:45,044
What's that day?

87
00:05:46,351 --> 00:05:51,254
The day she lost her dreams,
her love, her hopes... Everything.

88
00:05:54,058 --> 00:05:58,995
All that was left was
that necklace of memories...

89
00:06:00,432 --> 00:06:04,163
It's as precious as life to Lady Tsunade.

90
00:06:04,803 --> 00:06:08,466
It's really not something
to be offered in a bet.

91
00:06:09,641 --> 00:06:13,543
I don't care about that!
She bet it on her own, right?!

92
00:06:13,745 --> 00:06:17,272
Besides... that necklace is really
not something for you to wear.

93
00:06:17,348 --> 00:06:19,248
It's not just a necklace!

94
00:06:21,386 --> 00:06:23,820
It doesn't acknowledge anyone
other than Lady Tsunade.

95
00:06:24,522 --> 00:06:29,721
If someone else wears it,
that person inevitably...

96
00:06:31,095 --> 00:06:32,062
...dies!

97
00:06:54,853 --> 00:06:58,414
Nawaki, happy twelfth birthday!

98
00:07:01,092 --> 00:07:05,051
I'm not a kid anymore,
so I don't need gifts on my birthday!

99
00:07:05,196 --> 00:07:08,256
What're you saying?
You're still a kid, aren't you?!

100
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,530
But never mind that.
Hurry up and open your present!

101
00:07:11,703 --> 00:07:13,603
You'll definitely be pleased!

102
00:07:20,645 --> 00:07:23,011
Big Sister, could this be?

103
00:07:23,715 --> 00:07:28,516
Yes... It's the First Hokage's,
our grandfather's necklace!

104
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,287
I love you, Big Sister!

105
00:07:31,356 --> 00:07:33,517
I thought it'd be better than me having it.

106
00:07:34,492 --> 00:07:39,293
You've been wanting it all along, right?
Take good care of it.

107
00:07:39,964 --> 00:07:41,955
Not just this necklace!

108
00:07:43,067 --> 00:07:48,767
This village is grandfather's treasure!
I'm going to protect it!

109
00:07:49,674 --> 00:07:50,663
Nawaki...

110
00:07:51,276 --> 00:07:55,440
I'm the grandson of the Hokage who
built the Village Hidden in Leaves, so...!

111
00:07:56,648 --> 00:07:59,708
You said it.
Men don't go back on their word!

112
00:07:59,918 --> 00:08:00,577
Right!

113
00:08:00,852 --> 00:08:04,879
Someday, I'll become just like Grandfather.
And the Hokage name will be mine!

114
00:08:06,524 --> 00:08:09,687
Becoming the Hokage is my dream!

115
00:08:13,197 --> 00:08:15,165
Take off your headband, Nawaki.

116
00:08:16,668 --> 00:08:19,933
Just hurry up and take it off.
I have another present for you.

117
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,670
It's a charm to make
your dream come true.

118
00:08:51,636 --> 00:08:54,503
It's best if you don't look
at the remains.

119
00:08:55,607 --> 00:08:57,438
There's nothing wrong with that,
is there?

120
00:08:57,775 --> 00:08:59,402
Even if she were to look,

121
00:08:59,711 --> 00:09:02,407
she wouldn't be able to determine
that it's her little brother.

122
00:09:02,547 --> 00:09:03,809
Enough, Orochimaru!

123
00:09:04,649 --> 00:09:10,144
We are at war, now.
All Shinobi end up like this.

124
00:09:10,822 --> 00:09:13,723
There are no doctors on
the battlefield, so...

125
00:09:14,359 --> 00:09:18,159
However, children really get
much too excited, don't they?

126
00:09:18,763 --> 00:09:22,756
Especially on the day after
they receive a present.

127
00:09:33,378 --> 00:09:35,346
<i>Not just this necklace...</i>

128
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:43,815
<i>This village is grandfather's treasure!</i>
<i>I'm going to protect it!</i>

129
00:09:46,024 --> 00:09:48,720
First, in a mission where
a Four Man Cell must act alone

130
00:09:48,793 --> 00:09:52,092
for a long period of time
in enemy territory,

131
00:09:52,664 --> 00:09:56,031
by deploying one of the four
to be a medical specialist,

132
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:59,365
the survival rate as well as
the mission success rate

133
00:09:59,437 --> 00:10:01,064
should go up significantly.

134
00:10:01,606 --> 00:10:03,096
Therefore, establishing a framework

135
00:10:03,174 --> 00:10:04,937
to foster Ninja possessing
advanced medical skills

136
00:10:05,009 --> 00:10:06,567
and the development of
a medical institution

137
00:10:06,644 --> 00:10:11,513
should be considered
an urgent task for the present!

138
00:10:12,517 --> 00:10:16,317
Yes indeed, it's as you say.

139
00:10:17,021 --> 00:10:18,955
But we're in the middle of a war now.

140
00:10:19,557 --> 00:10:23,721
It takes too much time to
establish a medical framework.

141
00:10:23,895 --> 00:10:26,295
And at present,
we don't have enough knowledge...

142
00:10:26,898 --> 00:10:29,196
Enemies don't wait.

143
00:10:30,334 --> 00:10:32,199
What did you say?! Hey, old man!

144
00:10:32,770 --> 00:10:34,829
Then we'll never...

145
00:10:34,906 --> 00:10:37,136
I agree with her.

146
00:10:37,909 --> 00:10:42,107
I don't want the lives of the Shinobi
who died to be for naught.

147
00:10:42,513 --> 00:10:44,674
There should be something
we can learn from that.

148
00:10:48,386 --> 00:10:49,410
Excuse me!

149
00:10:50,388 --> 00:10:51,377
Thanks for earlier.

150
00:10:53,558 --> 00:10:55,753
What you said was right.

151
00:10:57,762 --> 00:10:58,626
Umm...

152
00:10:59,664 --> 00:11:02,360
It's late.
Shall I walk you home?

153
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:05,931
What? Is that okay with you?
Where's your home?

154
00:11:06,838 --> 00:11:07,862
The other way.

155
00:11:08,473 --> 00:11:09,838
Then don't bother.

156
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:14,008
I don't mind.
I also want to talk with you.

157
00:11:14,912 --> 00:11:19,178
And I would always use this path
to the Academy to pick up my little sister.

158
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,683
I loved this path.

159
00:11:21,152 --> 00:11:22,813
What? You loved?

160
00:11:23,888 --> 00:11:28,018
Yeah. In the battle when the Leaf
was attacked at night one year ago,

161
00:11:28,092 --> 00:11:29,354
my little sister was...

162
00:11:30,795 --> 00:11:34,026
<i>This man...is the same as me.</i>

163
00:11:50,815 --> 00:11:53,875
<i>Tomorrow's mission will be</i>
<i>within enemy lines...</i>

164
00:11:55,586 --> 00:12:00,387
Fighting and losing cherished people
is not the only way for a Shinobi.

165
00:12:00,892 --> 00:12:01,620
Uh huh.

166
00:12:01,926 --> 00:12:04,952
I'm living in a world of Shinobi
where death always hovers.

167
00:12:05,463 --> 00:12:09,456
I want to risk my life to bring
this war torn world under control.

168
00:12:10,601 --> 00:12:13,593
I love this village and my comrades.

169
00:12:14,205 --> 00:12:16,230
So I want to protect them.

170
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:22,145
Since my little sister died,
that sole thought has sustained me.

171
00:12:22,947 --> 00:12:24,972
So I'll become the Hokage...

172
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:26,983
An existence that protects everyone...

173
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:31,452
Becoming the Hokage is my dream.

174
00:12:39,764 --> 00:12:40,492
Dan...

175
00:12:46,838 --> 00:12:50,399
I'd like you... to take this.

176
00:12:57,215 --> 00:12:58,443
Hang on, Dan!

177
00:12:59,183 --> 00:13:03,745
Tsunade... I don't want... to die yet.

178
00:13:04,689 --> 00:13:09,251
I have many things that I must... do.

179
00:13:09,427 --> 00:13:10,587
Don't talk, Dan!

180
00:13:11,229 --> 00:13:13,163
<i>His kidney has been blown out...</i>

181
00:13:13,865 --> 00:13:16,993
<i>It's futile even for Tsunade</i>
<i>who is known as one of the Sannin...</i>

182
00:13:17,735 --> 00:13:22,638
I... must not... die here.

183
00:13:24,175 --> 00:13:26,609
It'll be okay. I stopped the bleeding.

184
00:13:27,545 --> 00:13:31,037
So it'll be okay... You'll be saved, Dan!

185
00:13:32,150 --> 00:13:33,174
Really?

186
00:13:34,986 --> 00:13:36,453
Thank goodness...

187
00:13:38,156 --> 00:13:39,851
Dan! Hang on!

188
00:13:40,324 --> 00:13:41,222
Dan!

189
00:13:45,496 --> 00:13:47,521
Dang it! Don't come out...

190
00:13:48,366 --> 00:13:50,766
Stop... Please stop!

191
00:13:51,369 --> 00:13:53,030
Stop... Stop...

192
00:13:53,704 --> 00:13:55,467
Stop... Stop...

193
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:59,406
Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

194
00:13:59,477 --> 00:14:00,239
Stop, I say!

195
00:14:00,311 --> 00:14:01,835
That's enough. He's dead!

196
00:14:31,642 --> 00:14:34,110
You understand, don't you, Naruto...?

197
00:14:35,546 --> 00:14:37,571
Ever since that day,

198
00:14:38,115 --> 00:14:40,583
Lady Tsunade has been...
in a constant turmoil.

199
00:14:49,026 --> 00:14:50,084
Naruto?

200
00:14:51,362 --> 00:14:54,160
I'm heading out... for training!

201
00:15:20,925 --> 00:15:22,552
Oh, you are already at it, I see!

202
00:15:22,627 --> 00:15:23,616
Hi, welcome!

203
00:15:24,629 --> 00:15:25,857
Why are you here?

204
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:29,290
You're cold. Don't say that.

205
00:15:30,601 --> 00:15:31,659
Master Jiraiya...

206
00:15:32,737 --> 00:15:36,503
Shizune, could you leave us?

207
00:15:37,074 --> 00:15:39,542
It's been a while.
I want to drink with her again.

208
00:15:40,511 --> 00:15:43,378
Master, <i>sake!</i> And some radish!

209
00:15:43,447 --> 00:15:44,141
Coming up!

210
00:15:48,085 --> 00:15:50,417
<i>I'm counting on you, Master Jiraiya.</i>

211
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:56,988
Your radish is ready.

212
00:15:57,061 --> 00:15:58,892
Ooh. This looks good.

213
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:07,833
At any rate, to think you'd still be taking
good care of that necklace...

214
00:16:08,372 --> 00:16:11,739
I thought you'd have lost it
long since to gambling.

215
00:16:13,377 --> 00:16:15,368
It's a memento of those two, right?

216
00:16:23,220 --> 00:16:24,778
Is he on your mind...?

217
00:16:25,089 --> 00:16:26,056
Who?

218
00:16:28,292 --> 00:16:29,554
Naruto.

219
00:16:31,028 --> 00:16:31,756
Not particularly...

220
00:16:32,964 --> 00:16:36,331
Still, it's immature,
taking on that kid as an opponent...

221
00:16:36,734 --> 00:16:40,727
He shouldn't be able to master
that Jutsu in a week, right?

222
00:16:41,339 --> 00:16:43,807
That's not what's called a bet.

223
00:16:46,243 --> 00:16:47,835
What's with the fit of despair?

224
00:16:49,113 --> 00:16:51,843
It's not a fit of despair!

225
00:16:53,784 --> 00:16:55,775
Are you going to meet
Orochimaru again?

226
00:16:57,588 --> 00:16:59,579
I can tell by looking at Shizune's face.

227
00:17:00,157 --> 00:17:03,923
I don't know what kind of deal
he proposed,

228
00:17:04,929 --> 00:17:06,897
but don't rush to a decision.

229
00:17:08,099 --> 00:17:12,229
And... let me just tell you one thing.

230
00:17:13,270 --> 00:17:15,204
The successive line of Hokages
have protected

231
00:17:15,272 --> 00:17:18,469
the Leaf Village and those living in it.

232
00:17:18,709 --> 00:17:23,078
They brought troubled times under control
and helped the village to prosper.

233
00:17:23,581 --> 00:17:25,606
They risked their lives
for this dream, this ideal!

234
00:17:27,718 --> 00:17:31,085
You're not someone who can't understand
the feelings of the previous Hokages.

235
00:17:32,556 --> 00:17:36,549
Just try doing something
to betray the Leaf Village

236
00:17:38,963 --> 00:17:42,421
When that happens, I'll kill you myself!

237
00:17:44,902 --> 00:17:47,427
It has nothing to do with me now!

238
00:17:48,606 --> 00:17:51,006
A person who has experienced
the death of people close to them

239
00:17:51,075 --> 00:17:53,168
and doesn't feel anything
is just a butcher.

240
00:17:54,879 --> 00:17:56,346
You're different, aren't you?

241
00:17:57,114 --> 00:18:01,210
No one cared for the welfare
of the villagers more than you.

242
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,317
At that time, too...

243
00:18:04,388 --> 00:18:06,481
That's enough with the lecture!

244
00:18:09,260 --> 00:18:13,128
Why... did you bring that kid?

245
00:18:13,597 --> 00:18:16,225
<i>Becoming the Hokage is my dream.</i>

246
00:18:18,702 --> 00:18:20,067
He resembles him, doesn't he?

247
00:18:20,704 --> 00:18:22,604
His age is about the same, too...

248
00:18:24,075 --> 00:18:25,042
<i>Not just that...</i>

249
00:18:30,681 --> 00:18:33,115
<i>Becoming the Hokage is my dream!</i>

250
00:18:36,887 --> 00:18:38,912
Geez, you do nothing,
but reckless things.

251
00:18:38,989 --> 00:18:40,081
Do you want to die?

252
00:18:40,524 --> 00:18:44,551
You're still a Genin,
so on the battlefield just run away.

253
00:18:44,695 --> 00:18:47,323
Don't tell a man to "run away!"

254
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:52,832
<i>That dream... And his cockiness as well...</i>

255
00:19:03,848 --> 00:19:09,309
No good! Dang it! Dang it!
Tomorrow, for sure!

256
00:19:11,288 --> 00:19:14,223
My head hurts.

257
00:19:15,526 --> 00:19:18,791
I totally got sick from drinking,
thanks to her...

258
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:28,395
<i>It seems Naruto never came home</i>
<i>last night...</i>

259
00:19:36,714 --> 00:19:39,444
<i>He's such a fool.</i>

260
00:19:51,896 --> 00:19:54,558
<i>Why don't we make a deal?</i>

261
00:19:55,399 --> 00:19:59,927
<i>I'll resurrect the little brother</i>
<i>and man, both of whom you loved...</i>

262
00:20:00,804 --> 00:20:03,967
<i>with the Forbidden Jutsu I've developed.</i>

263
00:20:05,676 --> 00:20:09,305
<i>Don't you want to see those two,</i>
<i>Tsunade?</i>

264
00:20:15,252 --> 00:20:16,480
<i>If I treat your arms...</i>

265
00:20:17,755 --> 00:20:19,689
<i>What do you intend to do with them?</i>

266
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:23,852
<i>This time, I will completely</i>
<i>destroy Leaf Village!</i>

267
00:20:24,295 --> 00:20:27,025
<i>No! You must not believe</i>
<i>in their sweet talk...</i>

268
00:20:27,898 --> 00:20:29,092
<i>Their wishes...</i>

269
00:20:29,166 --> 00:20:33,364
<i>Moreover, Tsunade, your wishes...</i>
<i>And dreams... Did you forget them?!</i>

270
00:20:33,637 --> 00:20:35,070
<i>I'll be straight with you.</i>

271
00:20:36,907 --> 00:20:41,276
<i>Tsunade, the village has demanded</i>
<i>that you become the Fifth Hokage.</i>

272
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:10,469
<i>I believe your promise,</i>
<i>its a true heart give me courage</i>

273
00:21:10,541 --> 00:21:14,875
<i>Always I feel it</i>
<i>the precious time with you</i>

274
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:19,007
<i>On your still shoulder</i>

275
00:21:20,251 --> 00:21:24,711
<i>I feel the wind that blows</i>
<i>towards tomorrow</i>

276
00:21:24,889 --> 00:21:30,327
<i>The city lights are like pieces of stars</i>

277
00:21:30,828 --> 00:21:35,128
<i>That hold us together</i>

278
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:44,838
<i>"Each one of us glows differently,"</i>

279
00:21:44,909 --> 00:21:47,503
<i>you say laughingly</i>

280
00:21:47,745 --> 00:21:53,411
<i>but you look most dazzling</i>

281
00:21:53,985 --> 00:21:58,354
<i>Like a comet,</i>

282
00:21:58,423 --> 00:22:04,521
<i>like the rainbow after the storm</i>

283
00:22:04,595 --> 00:22:11,694
<i>You bring light into my heart</i>

284
00:22:12,704 --> 00:22:22,079
<i>Being lost can be the answer</i>

285
00:22:23,414 --> 00:22:30,946
<i>Let's promise we won't cheat</i>

286
00:22:31,022 --> 00:22:35,015
<i>Uh...like a shooting star,</i>
<i>we do go ahead.</i>

287
00:22:37,929 --> 00:22:40,898
Darn it! What am I doing

288
00:22:40,965 --> 00:22:43,195
I fell asleep at such
an important time!

289
00:22:43,401 --> 00:22:45,562
Moreover, today is the day
of the bet!

290
00:22:45,636 --> 00:22:48,366
Meanwhile, I don't even know where
that old lady Tsunade has gone to!

291
00:22:48,706 --> 00:22:52,335
My training is not completed yet...

292
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:57,543
I've got to play it by ear
and rely on a one shot deal!

293
00:22:58,683 --> 00:23:01,982
Next time: "A Dubious Offer!
Tsunade's Choice"
